    <title>Playing the ABC Loose-Passive</title>
    <link rel="alternate" href="https://www.barge.org/blog/playing-the-abc-loose-passive" />
    <author>
      <name>Roy Cooke</name>
      <email>roycooke123@gmail.com (Roy Cooke)</email>
    </author>
    <updated>2016-09-07T02:37:14Z</updated>
    <published>2016-09-07T02:37:14Z</published>
    <summary type="text">ABC loose-passive’s are the easiest opponents to play against, and you generally have the largest edge against them. Most lowstakes players are ABC loose-passive. On the flop they tend to be fit or fold. Meaning, if they hit the flop, they continue, if not, they’ll fold.  The good news is they’re easily exploitable.</summary>
    <g-custom:tags type="string" />
