  <entry>
    <title>Understanding Equity and EV</title>
    <link rel="alternate" href="https://www.barge.org/understanding-equity-and-ev" />
    <author>
      <name>Roy Cooke</name>
      <email>roycooke123@gmail.com (Roy Cooke)</email>
    </author>
    <updated>2016-08-16T03:08:01Z</updated>
    <published>2016-08-16T03:08:01Z</published>
    <summary type="text">Many people don’t know the exact difference between equity and EV. In fact, some people use the terms as if they were identical.  Equity is the percentage chance that a hand will win after all the cards are dealt. The percentage chance includes splits and is utilized when comparing your holding against opponent’s hand(s) or range(s).</summary>
